    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-10-11T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-10-11T03:00:00-05:00" n="776"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d776">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760m.6111/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-10-11T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 11, 1939—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 11—10:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>723. My 721, October 10, 5 p.m. The Soviet-Lithuanian pact was signed last
                        night.<note n="49" xml:id="d776fn49">An English translation of this “Treaty
                        on the Transfer of the City of Vilno and Vilno Province to the Lithuanian
                        Republic and on Mutual Assistance between the Soviet Union and Lithuania” is
                        printed in the Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        December 16, 1939, p. 705.</note> I understand that it provides for a
                    15–year pact of mutual assistance similar to the Estonian and Latvian pacts with
                    the Soviet Union and permits the establishment of Soviet air bases and
                    garrisons, the number and location of which are undivulged in the present
                    agreement and are to be fixed by subsequent agreement. In return the Soviet
                    Union cedes to Lithuania the town of Vilna and the Vilna district.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Kaunas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
